ard.com/articles/news/dance/8546129/the-chainsmokers-kygo-family-video-rory-kramer|title=The Chainsmokers Honor Their Videographer Rory Kramer in Touching 'Family' Video With Kygo: Watch|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Mamo|first=Heran|date=December 12, 2019|accessdate=December 12, 2019}}</ref>\n|- \n! scope=\"row\"| \"Like It Is\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2020\n| Connor Brashier \n| <ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TOamHghGCfg Kygo, Zara Larsson, Tyga - Like It Is]</ref>\n|}\n\n== Production and songwriting credits ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+List of production and songwriting credits, showing original artists, year released and album name\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n! scope=\"col\"| Credit(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Written with:\n! scope=\"col\"| Produced with:\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Write On Me]]\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2016\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Fifth Harmony]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[7/27]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Co-writer/Producer\n| [[Stargate (production team)|Mikkel Eriksen]], [[Stargate (production team)|Tor Hermansen]], [[Priscilla Renea|Priscilla Hamilton]], [[Simon Wilcox]]\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Stargate (production team)|Stargate]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Squeeze\"\n| [[Stargate (production team)|Mikkel Eriksen]], [[Stargate (production team)|Tor Hermansen]], [[Sir Nolan|Nolan Lambroza]], [[Priscilla Renea|Priscilla Hamilton]], [[Simon Wilcox]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist-ua|refs=\n{{efn-ua|name=fn3|Remixes later made unavailable from Kygo's first official YouTube channel.}}\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Kygo}}\n\n[[Category:Discographies of Norwegian artists]]\n[[Category:Electronic music discographies]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Discography}}\n{{Infobox artist discography\n| Artist = [[Kygo]]\n| Image = Kygo i 2014.jpg\n| Caption = Kygo performing in 2014\n| Studio = 3\n| EP = 1\n| Singles = 24\n| Music videos = 19\n| Option name = Promotional singles\n| Option = 8\n| 2Option name = Remixes\n| 2Option = 13<!--Only include record label release-->\n}}\n\nNorwegian DJ [[Kygo]] has released two [[studio album]]s, one [[extended play]], 24 [[single (music)|single]]s, 8 [[promotional single]]s, 13 [[remix]]es<!--Only include record label release--> and 19 [[music video]]s.\n\n== Studio albums ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of studio albums, with selected chart positions, sales figures and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"10\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\"| [[VG-lista|NOR]]<br /><ref name=\"NOR\">{{cite web | url=http://norwegiancharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Kygo | title=Discography Kygo | publisher=Hung Medien | work=norwegiancharts.com | accessdate=18 November 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.9em;font-size:90%;\"| [[ARIA Charts|AUS]]<br /><ref name=\"AUS\">Peaks in Australia:\n* All except noted: {{cite web | url=http://australian-charts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Kygo | title=Discography Kygo | publisher=Hung Medien | work=australian-charts.com | accessdate=24 June 2015}}\n* \"Nothing Left\": {{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/aria-singles-one-direction-drag-me-down-is-no-1-20150808|title=ARIA Singles: One Direction 'Drag Me Down' Is No 1|publisher=Noise11|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|date=8 August 2015|accessdate=8 August 2015}}\n* \"Stole the Show\": {{cite web|url=http://www.noise11.com/news/aria-singles-justin-bieber-what-do-you-mean-spends-second-week-at-no-1-20150912|title=ARIA Singles: Justin Bieber 'What Do You Mean?' Spends Second Week At No 1|publisher=Noise11|last=Ryan|